                <head>No. 229.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Lowell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Frelinghuysen</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-05-29">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 29, 1883</date>. (Received June
                        9.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 557.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acquaint you that on the 21st
                    instant I received your No. 586 of the 5th instant, and immediately placed it in
                    the hands of the copyist. I was not able to make an appointment to communicate
                    it to Lord Granville for an earlier date than to-day. I have just now returned
                    from the foreign office, where I had an interview with his lordship, and read
                    this instruction to him, agreeably to your direction. I also left a copy of it
                    with him at his desire.</p>
                <p>I have, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>J. R. LOWELL.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
